text: Patissa tenuousa is a moth in the family Crambidae. It was described by Fu- Qiang Chen, Shi-Mei Song and Chun-Sheng Wu in 2007. It is found in Sichuan, China. The forewings are white with thin fuscous fasciae. ==References== Category:Moths described in 2007 Category:Schoenobiinae
title: Patissa tenuousa
